==Standard dialogue==
===If the player does not have a max cape in their bank or inventory===
* '''Player:''' Hello.
* {{tbox|The man glances at you and grunts something unintelligible.}}
* {{topt|Who are you?}}
** '''Player:''' Who are you?
** '''Mac:''' Mac. What's it to you?
** '''Player:''' Only trying to be friendly.
** {{tact|previous}}
* {{topt|What do you have in your sack?}}
** '''Player:''' What do you have in your sack?
** {{tcond|If the player does not have a total level of 2376:}}
*** '''Mac:''' None of yer bis'ness.
*** '''Player:''' How rude! I was only being curious.
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{tcond|If the player has a total level of 2376:}}
*** '''Mac:''' S'me cape.
*** '''Player:''' Your cape?
*** {{topt|What does your cape do?}}
**** '''Player:''' What does your cape do?
**** '''Mac:''' All the things other skillcapes do.
**** {{topt|Can you tell me what they are?}}
***** '''Player:''' Can you tell me what they are?
***** '''Mac:''' Fine... Ajjat gave me unlimited teleports to his Warrior's guild and Kamfreena lets me fight her Cyclopes without needing those annoying tokens.
***** '''Mac:''' Melee combat tutor added a ring of life function and the armour salesman at the Ranging guild added a magnet and undead chicken thing.
***** '''Mac:''' Brother Jered attached a holy wrench and Wizard Sinina enchanted the cape so I can change me spellbook.
***** '''Mac:''' Aubury attached all of the runecrafting tiaras, an estate agent sold me some teleports and one of the nurses at the Emir's Arena made it give me faster hitpoints.
***** '''Mac:''' Agility Arena guy with a Parrot pet made it lighter for me and Kaqemeex convinced the Nardah herbalist to make potions for me if I wear it and he attached a pestle and mortar, toos.
***** '''Mac:''' Martin Thwait made the cape better for being sneaky and the Master Crafter added a teleport to his guild before Hickton attached some grapples and a crossbow.
***** '''Mac:''' Duradel convinced all Slayer masters to give me a chance at repeating an assignment and the Hunting Expert added some useful teleports, too.
***** '''Mac:''' A dwarf gave it a chance to give me extra ores and another dwarf made it give more experience when making gold bars and the Master Chef stopped it from burning any food.
***** '''Mac:''' Ignatius Vulcan added a torch for lighting up caves and the Woodcutting tutor made it easier to find bird's nests and Martin the Master Farmer made it yield more herbs.
***** '''Mac:''' So yeah all of that.
